sec.p:
To achieve energy transition aimed at decarbonising energy demand and energy production, a complementary energy system based on hydrogen can be developed to provide the necessary flexibility by:
enabling cost-effective energy storage both in the short- and long-term;
allowing energy and, more specifically, electricity consumption and production to be decoupled both geographically and temporally;
helping to stabilise energy prices in the face of variable wind and solar power production;
facilitating cost-efficient bulk transport over long distances using pipelines, ships and trucks.
making energy sector and regional coupling possible.
